Three police officers were among the more than 1000
suspects which were arrested over the weekend.Constables from Khutsong, Sandringham and Protea Glen
were arrested for crimes ranging from robbery to extortion and corruption.A constable in Sandringham, Joburg, was arrested for
attempted robbery, misuse of a state vehicle and defeating the ends of justice.if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");<a href="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/jump?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" target="_blank"><img src="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/ad?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" border="0" alt=""></a>This is after the constable allegedly worked with three
suspects to rob a business in Linbro Park, Joburg North.In another incident, a constable based in Khutsong, West
Rand, was arrested for extortion and kidnapping a 36-year-old foreign national
in Potchefstoom, North West.He and five others were arrested after the family member
of the kidnapped received a ransom fee and alerted the police.In Protea Glen, Soweto, a constable was arrested for
corruption, extortion and fraud.He was arrested by the Gauteng Anti-corruption unit for
allegedly trying to extort a R30 0000 bribe from people he had promised jobs to
at the Joburg Metro Police Department.About 348 suspects were arrested in Ekurhuleni for
various crimes including rape, house-breaking, possession of suspected stolen
vehicles, possession of dagga and assault, among others.A total of 444 suspects were bust by the Tshwane police
for crimes like business robbery, pointing of a firearm, possession of dagga
and driving under the influence of alcohol.All of the arrested suspects are expected to appear in
various Gauteng magistrate courts on Monday, according to Police Spokesman
Captain Mavela Masondo.